This paper is about improving the performance of non-autoregressive neural machine translation (NAT) models, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the cs.CL (Computation and Language) category. The proposed model also involves the use of neural networks and optimization techniques, which are common in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) categories. Additionally, the model's performance is evaluated on various datasets, which is a common practice in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of image captioning as a potential application, which falls under the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category.
